sequenceDiagram
    participant W as Worker
    participant Q as Queue
    participant C as Consumer
    participant DO as LinkProcessorDO
    participant Ext as External API
    participant TG as Telegram

    Note over W: Telegram webhook arrives

    W->>Q: env.LINK_QUEUE.send({url, orgId, source: "telegram", sourceMeta: {chatId, messageId}})
    W-->>TG: return 200 immediately

    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        Note over Q,DO: CASE 1: Processing succeeds
        Q->>C: Deliver message
        C->>DO: ingestAndProcess(message)
        DO->>DO: sync store (livePull)
        DO->>DO: dedup check → new link
        DO->>DO: commit linkCreated (source + meta)
        DO->>Ext: fetchMetadata
        Ext-->>DO: metadata ✅
        DO->>DO: AI summary ✅
        DO->>DO: commit linkProcessingCompleted
        DO-->>C: { status: "completed" }
        C->>Q: message.ack() ✅
        DO->>TG: Api.react() 👍
    end

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note over Q,DO: CASE 2: Processing fails, failure committed
        Q->>C: Deliver message
        C->>DO: ingestAndProcess(message)
        DO->>DO: sync store → dedup → commit linkCreated
        DO->>Ext: fetchMetadata
        Note over Ext: ⏱ hangs...
        Note over DO: Effect.timeout fires at 10s
        DO->>DO: catchAllCause → commit linkProcessingFailed
        DO-->>C: { status: "failed" }
        C->>Q: message.ack() ✅ (failure is committed)
        DO->>TG: Api.react() 👎
        Note over TG: User can retry from UI ("Regenerate")
    end

    rect rgb(255, 235, 238)
        Note over Q,DO: CASE 3: DO unreachable (infra failure)
        Q->>C: Deliver message
        C-xDO: ingestAndProcess(message) — DO crashed / store dead
        Note over C: HTTP call fails, no commit possible
        C->>Q: message NOT acked → queue retries
        Note over Q: Retry after delay (max 3 attempts)
        Q->>C: Redeliver (attempt 2)
        C->>DO: ingestAndProcess(message)
        DO->>DO: fresh wake → sync → dedup → already committed → process
        DO-->>C: { status: "completed" }
        C->>Q: message.ack() ✅
    end
